# 🐍 **Python Learning Path: A Structured Roadmap**

A **step-by-step guide** to mastering Python, from **absolute beginner** to **advanced developer**, with **projects, resources, and certifications** to solidify your knowledge.

---

## 🎯 **Stage 1: Foundations**

### **1.1 Python Basics**

✅ **Syntax & Data Types** – Variables, `int`, `str`, `list`, `dict`, `tuple`, `set`.  
✅ **Control Flow** – `if`/`else`, `for`/`while` loops, `match` (Python 3.10+).  
✅ **Functions** – Defining functions, parameters, return values, lambda functions.  
✅ **Input/Output** – `print()`, `input()`, file handling (`open()`, `read()`, `write()`).

📌 **Resources**:  
📘 _[Python Crash Course](https://nostarch.com/pythoncrashcourse2e)_ (Book)  
🎥 [Corey Schafer’s Python Basics](https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PL-osiE80TeTskrapNbzXhwoFUiLCjGgY7) (YouTube)  
🌐 [Official Python Tutorial](https://docs.python.org/3/tutorial/)

🎯 **Practice**:

- Complete **20+ katas** on [Codewars](https://codewars.com/) (Level **8–6 Kyu**).

---

## 🚀 **Stage 2: Intermediate Skills**

### **2.1 Core Concepts**

✅ **Modules & Packages** – `import`, creating your own modules, `pip`.  
✅ **Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)** – Classes, attributes, methods, inheritance, encapsulation.  
✅ **Error Handling** – `try`/`except`, `raise`, `finally`, custom exceptions.  
✅ **File Operations** – `open()`, `json`, `csv`, `pickle` modules.

### **2.2 Hands-on Projects**

🔹 **CLI To-Do List App** – Practice file handling, error handling.  
🔹 **Web Scraper** – Use `requests` + `BeautifulSoup` to extract data from websites.

📌 **Resources**:  
📘 _[Automate the Boring Stuff](https://automatetheboringstuff.com/)_ (Projects + Automation)  
🛠️ [Real Python](https://realpython.com/) (Guides + Tutorials)

🎯 **Practice**:

- Solve **30+ problems** on [LeetCode](https://leetcode.com/) (**Easy & Medium**).

---

## 🔥 **Stage 3: Advanced Topics**

### **3.1 Deep Dive into Python**

✅ **Decorators & Generators** – `@staticmethod`, `@property`, `yield`.  
✅ **Concurrency & Parallelism** – `threading`, `multiprocessing`, `asyncio`.  
✅ **Advanced OOP** – Metaclasses, abstract classes, `dataclasses`.  
✅ **Testing & Debugging** – `pytest`, `unittest`, `pdb`, logging.

### **3.2 Frameworks & Libraries**

🔹 **Web Development** – Flask/Django (build a REST API).  
🔹 **Data Science & AI** – `pandas`, `numpy`, `matplotlib`, `scikit-learn`.  
🔹 **Automation & Scripting** – `selenium`, `openpyxl`, `pyautogui`.

📌 **Projects**:  
🖥️ **Build a Blog** – Full-stack web app using Django.  
📈 **Data Analysis Dashboard** – Use **Jupyter Notebooks** and `matplotlib`.

🎯 **Practice**:

- Solve **50+ problems** on [LeetCode](https://leetcode.com/) (**Medium & Hard**).

---

## 🧩 **Stage 4: Specializations**

### **4.1 Choose Your Track**

#### **➡️ Web Development**

- 🎓 [Full Stack Python](https://www.fullstackpython.com/)
- 📚 _[Flask Web Development](https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/flask-web-development/9781491991725/)_

